A Kabusa Grade I Area Court on Wednesday sentenced an applicant to one year in prison for damaging a transformer belonging to the Abuja Electricity Distribution Company (AEDC). The judge, Ibrahim Kagarko, sentenced Ibrahim Ali, after he pleaded guilty to mischief and theft. Kagarko did not give the convict an option to pay any fine. Earlier, the prosecution counsel, Mahmud Lawal, informed the court that Mr Effiong Etim who works with AEDC, reported the case at the Garki Police Station, FCT on August 20. Lawal told the court that the complainant reported that on August 20, Ali removed a transformer panel door from the AEDC facility located at Arochukwu Street, Garki II. Lawal informed the court that in the course of police investigation, it was discovered that the convict had caused inestimable damage to the transformer. The convict, he also said, confessed to the crime when interrogated by the police. The offence contravened sections 327 and 287 of the Penal Code Law, he added. (NAN)  2 scavengers to do 15 days community service for vandalism Courts jails  man for riding  motorcycle in Abuja Trader bags 10 monthsâ€™ imprisonment for duping customer of N35,000 Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin